HEADWORD: Shropshire
<hw>Shrop"shire</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From
<etsep>Shropshire</etsep>, country of England.]</ety> <def>An English
breed of black-faced hornless sheep similar to the Southdown, but
larger, now extensively raised in many parts of the world.</def>⟦br⟧
